To install Gimp# you will need Mono. Gimp# will only work with GIMP 2.1.x
or GIMP 2.2 (pre).

Building Gimp# is easy:

1) unpack the archive
2) % cd gimp-sharp-0.3
3) % make
4) become root
5) % make install

The files will be installed in your GIMP plug-in directory, for
example in /usr/local/lib/gimp/2.0/plug-ins/

At the moment Gimp# will install 3 plug-ins for you:

/Filters/Artistic/Ministeck
/Filters/Render/NCP
/Filters/Render/Picture Package